(39531, '7EEC08F2-4E4E-415E-8C93-C0A1FF086A64', 'Love, so happy you had a good night’s sleep. I had a rocky one, just up at 4 turning over the last week. I know I made mistakes aside from being evasive and not pushing sooner to have a conversation with Ilsa. I’m feeling confused on the feedback and guidance on how to handle strong emotions both from you and when I feel them in reaction to your own communications and interactions with other men. Some of this is my own history, where I’ve developed protective patterns of avoidance and feeling insecure and sometimes confused on how to draw boundaries….I take in the emotion from everywhere and i want to do the right thing and I want to protect myself and be a loving partner to you and be a fair and kind friend … and when these things are in tension…it can be difficult for me to navigate. Difficult is an understatement. I felt on the edge of a breakdown the other night and literally had to retreat to the womb of the hot tub to loose it and try and find comfort.  Part of me still feels like “what the hell happened?” How did we crossover into such dark territory? I never want to go here again. I can’t…I know you can’t.   I know all of these hurt you tremendously and I have terrible shame and guilt around this and am also feeling a bit defensive and confused.  I want to work through what we can together to repair and Continue my own work, intensively, to re-wire some of my own patterns. (Some parts of Bewilderment come To mind actually…look forward to discussing). I love you so very much, with all my ever-expanding fractured and bruised heart…and I want to hold you and wrap myself around you so you feel both love and protected by me. I don’t want that ever To change. ', '660759348404211584', 'None', 1, 'David', 'Nitzan', 0, '', '', '', 'iMessage', 'E:nwdave@b-zb.com', 'David', '2021-12-09T08:15:48.404212'),
